{% comment %}
  Search page header displaying search terms and results count.
  Shows search feedback and handles no results scenarios.

  Features:
  - Search term display with results count
  - Dynamic results counting (products only)
  - No results message and suggestions
  - Search performed state detection
  - Responsive typography and spacing

  Content states:
  - Search performed with results: Shows count and terms
  - Search performed with no results: Shows no results message
  - No search performed: Shows default search state

  Layout:
  - Search heading with italic styling
  - Large result count with search terms
  - Conditional messaging based on results
  - Responsive margins and spacing

  Dependencies:
  - Search liquid object with results and terms
  - Localization for all text content
  - Responsive design system classes

  Usage:
  - Always used at top of search results page
  - Provides context for search state
  - Guides user experience with clear messaging
{% endcomment %}

{% liquid
  assign products_results = search.results | where: 'object_type', 'product'
%}

<div class='mx-sm my-lg lg:m-lg 2xl:mx-0'>
  <h1 class='h5 italic mb-2xs'>
    {{ 'general.search.search' | t }}
  </h1>
  <h2 class='h1' sub-section-id='MainSearchResultsCount'>
    {{ 'templates.search.results_with_count' | t: terms: search.terms, count: products_results.size }}
  </h2>
  {%- if search.performed and products_results.size == 0 -%}
    <p class='text-body mb-sm'>
      {{ 'templates.search.no_results' | t: terms: search.terms }}
    </p>
  {%- endif -%}
</div>

{% schema %}
{
  "name": "t:sections.main-search-hero.name",
  "enabled_on": {
    "templates": ["search"]
  },
  "presets": [
    {
      "name": "t:sections.main-search-hero.name"
    }
  ]
}
{% endschema %}
